# BROWSER-publish.md - Substack Newsletter Publishing Patterns

## SS 8. Create & Publish Newsletter Post

### Step 1 — Navigate to editor

Navigate directly to `{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post` — creates a new draft immediately.

```
exec openclaw browser --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} navigate "https://{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post" 2>&1
```

🚨 **Do NOT use "Create" button on dashboard** — it does not reliably open the post editor.
🚨 **Do NOT use "New post" nav button** — it opens the Notes composer, NOT the article editor.

### Step 2 — Fill title and subtitle

Title and subtitle use `<textarea>`, NOT contenteditable.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    var titleTA = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder="Title"]');
    var subtitleTA = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder*="subtitle"]');

    if (titleTA) {
      titleTA.focus();
      titleTA.value = ${JSON.stringify(title)};
      titleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
      titleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    }

    if (subtitleTA) {
      subtitleTA.focus();
      subtitleTA.value = ${JSON.stringify(subtitle)};
      subtitleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
      subtitleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    }

    return { titleSet: !!titleTA, subtitleSet: !!subtitleTA };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 3 — Write body content

🚨 **Body uses `div[contenteditable="true"]` (ProseMirror/TipTap editor).** First one on page is the body editor.
🚨 **Clear first** (editor may have default subscribe/thanks blocks).
🚨 **Paste as HTML** — the editor accepts rich HTML and renders it correctly.

**Supported HTML formatting (verified 2026-03-28):**
- `<h2>` — section headings
- `<strong>` — bold
- `<em>` — italic
- `<a href="...">` — links (including Substack profile links like `https://substack.com/@handle`)
- `<ul><li>` — bullet lists
- `<blockquote><p>` — blockquotes
- `<p>` — paragraphs

🚨 **@mentions via HTML paste do NOT work** — the `substack-mention` span bleeds content. Reference writers via `<a href="https://substack.com/@handle">Name</a>` links instead.
🚨 **Hashtags are NOT supported** in the newsletter editor (Notes only).

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    var editor = document.querySelectorAll('div[contenteditable="true"]')[0];
    if (!editor) return { error: 'no editor' };

    // Clear existing content
    editor.focus();
    document.execCommand('selectAll');
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300));
    document.execCommand('delete');
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));

    var html = ${JSON.stringify(bodyHtml)};

    // Paste as HTML for rich formatting
    var dt = new DataTransfer();
    dt.setData('text/html', html);
    dt.setData('text/plain', 'fallback');
    editor.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', {
      clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true
    }));

    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));

    // Fallback if paste didn't work
    if (editor.innerText.length < 100) {
      document.execCommand('insertText', false, html);
    }

    return { typed: true, len: editor.innerText.length };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 4 — Wait for auto-save

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var saved = btns.find(b => /saved/i.test(b.innerText.trim()));
    return { saved: saved ? saved.innerText.trim() : 'not found' };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 5 — Open publish settings and configure

Click "Continue" button to open publish panel.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var continueBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Continue');
    if (!continueBtn) return { error: 'no Continue button' };
    continueBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));

    // Set Audience to Everyone (first radio group, name=audience)
    var radios = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input[type="radio"]'));
    var audienceEveryone = radios.find(r => r.name === 'audience' && r.value === 'everyone');
    if (audienceEveryone && !audienceEveryone.checked) {
      audienceEveryone.click();
      audienceEveryone.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    }

    // Re-query radios (DOM may update after audience change)
    radios = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input[type="radio"]'));

    // Set Comments to Everyone (second radio group, name=commentLevel)
    var commentEveryone = radios.find(r => r.name === 'commentLevel' && r.value === 'everyone');
    if (commentEveryone && !commentEveryone.checked) {
      commentEveryone.click();
      commentEveryone.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    }

    radios = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input[type="radio"]'));
    var state = radios.map(r => ({ name: r.name, value: r.value, checked: r.checked }));
    return { settingsOpen: true, radios: state };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

🚨 **Both radio groups default to "only_paid" (verified 2026-03-28).** MUST set BOTH to "everyone":
- First group (`name="audience"`): `value="everyone"` vs `value="only_paid"`
- Second group (`name="commentLevel"`): `value="everyone"` vs `value="only_paid"` vs `value="none"`

### Step 6 — Publish

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var publishBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Send to everyone now');
    if (!publishBtn) return { error: 'no publish button' };
    publishBtn.click();
    return { clicked: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

🚨 **After clicking "Send to everyone now"**, the page navigates to share-center. This will cause `Execution context was destroyed` error — this is NORMAL and means publish succeeded.

### Step 7 — Verify published

Wait 3s for navigation, then check:

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var isLive = document.body.innerText.includes('Your post is live');
    var url = window.location.href;
    return { published: isLive, url: url };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

Success indicators:
- URL contains `/share-center`
- Page text contains "Your post is live!"
- Post appears on `{{handle}}.substack.com`

